{n \choose k} p^k (1 - p)^{n-k}
p \in [0, 1]
\frac{ {n \choose k} p^k (1 - p)^{n-k} }{\int_0^1 {n \choose k} p^k (1 - p)^{n-k}} = \frac{ p^k (1 - p)^k }{ \int_0^1 p^k (1 - p)^{n-k} \, dp}.
\mathbb{P}(a \le p \le b) = \frac{\int_a^b p^k (1 - p)^{n-k} \, dp }{\int_0^1 p^k (1 - p)^{n-k} \, dp}.
